I run all my movies through VirtualDubMob, File,Open --> save as AVI, make sure Direct Stream Copy is chosen and this usually fixes issues related to the sound or picture for me. Sometimes the files have issues with sound latency or syncing, not sure why but who cares if it gets fixed. This works for 99.9% of avi files and only takes about 30-40 secs. I copy it to flash drive and plug directly into dvd and works. Try it if it doesn't work just remember ITS FREE!. Cheers for upload.
